.TH VV-CONTEXT-ACCEPT 1 "2026-03-11" "vv 0.8.0-1-g0b66d30" "Vibe-Vault Manual"
.SH NAME
vv-context-accept \- accept or pin outdated command updates
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B vv context accept [\-\-project <name>] [\-\-file <name>] [\-\-keep\-mine]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Resolves outdated command notifications from "vv context sync".
.PP
Without \-\-keep\-mine, the pending template update replaces the current command.
With \-\-keep\-mine, a .pinned marker is written so future syncs skip the file.
.PP
Without \-\-file, all pending updates are processed.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-project <name>
Override auto\-detected project name
.TP
.B \-\-file <name>
Accept only this file (e.g. wrap.md)
.TP
.B \-\-keep\-mine
Pin current version instead of accepting the update
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
vv context accept                                    Accept all pending updates
vv context accept \-\-file wrap.md                     Accept one update
vv context accept \-\-file wrap.md \-\-keep\-mine         Pin your version
vv context accept \-\-project myproject \-\-keep\-mine    Pin all for a project
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR vv (1),
.BR vv\-context (1),
.BR vv\-context\-sync (1),
.BR vv\-context\-diff (1)
